<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<chapter xml:id="set_theory" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Set Theory</title>

    <introduction>
        <p>
            Some very basic concepts of set theory. This is meant to review set theory so one can be comfortable reading and manipulating most
            mathematical objects. This is neither an 'introduction to proofs' type of chapter, we do not explain logic, induction, etc. Nor is
            it an formal axiomatic study.
        </p>
    </introduction>
